    "body": "## Problem\n\n`v:event` and `:help event-data` are semantically the same concept, but because of historical baggage they behave (and are documented) differently. And `nvim_exec_autocmds()` can't set `v:event` fields which may be required for the executed event to actually work correctly.\n\nAlso, `nvim_exec_autocmds()` can't set these event fields:\n\n```\n • file: (string) <afile> (not expanded to a full path)\n • match: (string) <amatch> (expanded to a full path)\n • buf: (number) <abuf>\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n1. When executing the Lua handler for an event, Nvim should directly set the `data` object from any `v:event` fields. Then it should apply any `data` set by the `nvim_exec_autocmds()` caller (which may overwrite the fields). Then Lua event handlers never need to look at `vim.v.event`.\n2. Deprecate `v:event`, recommend Lua handlers instead.\n\n## Open questions\n\nHaven't thought about whether it makes sense to allow `nvim_exec_autocmds` to override `file`/`match`/`buf`.",
